    "description": "The Gene Loss Database (GLossDB) is a curated resource for information on gene loss events in mammalian species, initially focusing on cetaceans. It centralizes and presents data in a user-friendly format, including the mechanism of gene loss, supporting evidence, and links to original publications.",
